Time: 10:00am
Where: Charter School of Education Excellence
What: 2020 Athletic Award (Outdoor)

Charter School of Educational Excellence, one of New York’s highest-performing charter schools, holds socially distanced, outdoor athletics awards galas to celebrate accomplishments of student athletes during the 2019-20 academic year. Also awards inaugural Daniel Reyes-Goldberg Scholarship, named for an accomplished Yonkers scholar-athlete and public servant who died in 2013 at age 33.

post_text:
The Nest if the OWL (Video #5/Football)

Charter School of Educational Excellence “ LIVE “ Celebrating the 5th Athletic Banquet Event.

CSEE Founder and Board Chair Eduardo LaGuerre said: “Athletics provide a vital component to a students' social emotional and physical wellness. Education-based athletics are a great way for scholars to learn core life values including teamwork, accountability, discipline, work-ethic and passion. Our athletics culture is not only nurturing but student centered. Coaches, administration, teachers, board members, and the greater community are fully devoted to the program and the endless beneficial impacts it has for the students and future leaders of our society."

We do NOT own the music license been played on the background.

CSEE is not just about academics but also about kindness and Community.

VIDEO #2

YONKERS, NY – The Charter School of Educational Excellence (CSEE) holds a drive-thru graduation ceremony for 8th graders today Tuesday, June 23 at its main campus, 260 Warburton Avenue, Yonkers, starting at 9 am (schedule below).

“Nothing will stop us from celebrating our graduating scholars,” CSEE Founder and Board Chair Eduardo LaGuerre said. “Our students, families and staff have stayed committed and strong throughout this unprecedented experience and they deserve the fullest recognition and accolades.”

In today’s age it’s very important to use the Internet in a responsible and safe manner.

This program #AlticeConnectSmart is sponsoring the Literacy Education Curriculum in selected schools across the Country as part of its commitment to digital wellness and helping students stay safe online. The course is provided by #EVERFI and geared towards kids in grades 5-9 and includes 3-4 hours of engaging, gamifield learning, helping students understand the risks and rewards of technology while tackling issues including privacy, security, cyber-bullying, digital relationships and digital addiction.

Westchester County Legislator Mr Nader Sayegh was a guest speaker

Please SHARE this message/video
https://youtu.be/4-FsJMqr9a0

Dear CSEE Parents and Guardians,

CSEE is happy to announce our dates for our information sessions for admission and lottery for the 2020-2021 school year. The Charter School of Educational Excellence will be accepting applications for children entering grades K-9 in the fall of 2020. There will be approximately 75 open seats for Kindergarten, and a few seats open for grades 1-9 depending on grade availability.

Because many families choose to register their child(ren) at CSEE, it is important that if you are planning to have your child attend CSEE that you complete and submit the Lottery Application for the 2020-2021 school year in a timely manner.

INFORMATIONAL SESSIONS:
November 19, 2019 at 9:00 AM
December 12, 2019 at 2:00 PM
January 8, 2020 at 9:00 AM
January 23, 2020 at 4:30 PM
February 13, 2020 at 4:30 PM
March 4, 2020 at 9:00 AM
March 19, 2020 at 5:00 PM

ADDRESS:
Charter School of Educational Excellence
260 Warburton Avenue
Yonkers, NY 10701

For more information, please call 914-476-5070, Ext. 18.

Save the Date & Register!

CSEE is proud to announce our 2nd Annual GIRLS ON THE RUN EVENT!! The event will be held on Saturday, November 23, 2019 at Rockland Lake located in Valley Cottage, NY.

post_text:
HOW CHARTER SCHOOL OF EDUCATIONAL EXCELLENCE EMPHASIZES LIFE LESSONS IN SPORTS

Yonkers, NY— A few years ago, Michael DeSimone attended a PCA event with the Westchester Knicks. From that moment forward, he was sold on the potential impact of PCA programs. DeSimone, the Physical Education, Health & Athletic Director at Charter School of Educational Excellence (CSEE) needed to take the next step, so only a few months ago, started a partnership with Positive Coaching Alliance-New York City. According to DeSimone, "the program has gotten so big that culture is a huge component now. Bringing in PCA was a no brainer."

post_text:
Los directivos de Charter School of Educational Excellence (CSEE), ubicada en Yonkers, fueron felicitados por oficiales del Departamento de Educación del Estado de Nueva York (NYSED), por los recientes resultados en los grados escolares de sus alumnos, del período educativo 2017-2018, que sobrepasan a los estudiantes del mismo nivel de las escuelas públicas de Yonkers, del condado de Westchester y de todo el estado de Nueva York, en Inglés y Matemáticas.

“Estamos felices por estos logros. Hemos recibido felicitaciones del NYSED y eso nos motiva a seguir trabajando fuerte por la educación de nuestros alumnos”, dijo Sobeida Cruz, fundadora y miembro de la junta directiva de CSEE, quien explicó que todos estos logros son del trabajo conjunto de maestros, padres y alumnos.

post_text:
Board of Regents Approves Yonkers Charter High School

Over the summer, the New York State Board of Regents approved a request by the Charter School for Educational Excellence to expand its school from its current kindergarten to grade eight classes, to include grades nine through 12 and the first Yonkers Charter High School. The new high school will welcome its first class of 100 freshman in the fall of 2019 at the former Our Lady of Rosary church and school, which is located next to the existing CSEE.
